**Segments**

- **Consulting Services**: The consulting services segment of the HSE industry involves providing expert advice and guidance to organizations regarding health, safety, and environmental practices. These services may include risk assessments, regulatory compliance audits, safety management system development, and on-site evaluations to identify potential hazards and formulate strategies for improvement.

- **Training Services**: The training services segment of the HSE market focuses on educating employees and management on best practices for maintaining a safe and healthy work environment. This can encompass a wide range of topics such as emergency response training, hazard communication, personal protective equipment usage, and regulatory compliance training to ensure that all stakeholders are well-informed and equipped to prevent accidents and mitigate risks.

- **Compliance Services**: Compliance services within the HSE consulting and training sector revolve around ensuring that organizations adhere to relevant health, safety, and environmental regulations. This includes conducting audits, developing compliance strategies, maintaining records, and implementing corrective actions to address any non-compliance issues identified. By staying up-to-date with changing regulations, companies can avoid fines, legal repercussions, and reputation damage.

